node.contents: Based on the class being named PhoneBook, I assume that you ultimately want to create a mapping between a phone number, and a person. If this is what you need to do then your PhoneBook class should contain a Map instead of a List (but this may depend on other parameters of the project).

node.contents: In the above, the phone number is represented as a String, which is probably not ideal since the same phone number could have different String representations (different spacing, or dashes, etc). Ideally the Map key would be a PhoneNumber class that takes this all into account in its hashCode and equals functions.
